						<div class="postbody">Hello, im posting again with a little tiny problem i have involving Zero Page ... Y register<br /><br />Sometimes i need to use a LDA &quot;zero page&quot; RAM in some places, which is &quot;B9 xx 00&quot;<br />the problem is, i cant figure out how to actually do it, cause i always get &quot;incorrect addressing mode&quot; error no matter what i try, how many times i try.<br /><br />This is for &quot;NESASM 2.51 autoZP&quot; version. i dont know if it's a bug or not. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> The only way i can ever make it work is by manually typing out a .db command with the actual hex numbers.<br /><br />I tried LDA ($41),y ... LDA [$41],y ... LDA ($41,y) ...LDA [$41,y] ... the weird accented brackets like { and } ...i tried everything i can possibly think of and nothing works <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> except just a plain .db only<br />is there some way to do it ??<br /><br /><img src="https://i.imgur.com/TcudduH.png" alt="Image" /></div>

					
