					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For a good comprehensive reference on which instructions exist, I recommend this:<br /><a href="http://www.obelisk.me.uk/6502/reference.html#LDY" class="postlink">http://www.obelisk.me.uk/6502/reference.html#LDY</a><br /><br /><strong>$B9</strong> is <strong>LDA absolute, Y</strong> though; it is neither LDY nor zero page. You can point absolute addresses at the zero page if you need to, however.<br /><br />There is a <strong>LDX/STX zero page, Y</strong>, which I think is the only instruction with that kind of addressing?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
