				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">LDA $41,Y (B9 41 00) calculates the effective address by adding Y to $0041.<br /><br />LDA [$41],Y (B1 41) calculates the effective address by reading the bytes at $0042 and $0041, forming a 16-bit number out of them, and adding Y.<br /><br />If NESASM is assembling LDA $41,Y as B1 41, it is misbehaving. Auto-ZP should not activate for aaaa,Y mode unless the instruction is LDX, which is the only official instruction on the 6502 to have both aaaa,Y and dd,Y versions.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
